headline: Johnson Controls launches YORK YDAM: the ultimate high-density chiller for multistory data centers and AI factories
summary: Johnson Controls (NYSE: JCI), the global leader for smart, healthy and sustainable buildings, today announced its newest innovation in data center thermal management, the YORK YDAM air-cooled magnetic bearing centrifugal chiller. The innovative chiller is purpose-built to overcome the complex space and site challenges in high-density, multistory data centers. headline: Is It Too Late To Consider Johnson Controls International (JCI) After Its 62% One-Year Rally?
summary: If you are wondering whether Johnson Controls International is priced fairly after its strong run, it helps to step back and separate share price excitement from underlying value. The stock last closed at US$122.98, with returns of 6.9% over 7 days, 0.5% over 30 days, 0.5% year to date, 62.2% over 1 year, 98.6% over 3 years and 163.5% over 5 years.
